definition.value: A nitrotoluene that is 2-nitrotoluene carrying two hydroxy substituents at positions 4 and 5.
A member of the class of monohydroxy-1,4-benzoquinones that is 2-hydroxy-1,4-benzoquinone carrying an additional methyl substituent at position 5.
A 2,4-dihydroxy-5-methyl-6-oxo-2,4-hexadienoic acid in which both double bonds adopt a cis-configuration.
A decaprenyl diphosphate having (Z)-stereochemistry about all but one of the double bonds.
An acyl-CoA resulting from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the 1-carboxy group of (2S)-methylsuccinic acid.
